\f1\b \cf19 Unvalidated user input
\f0\b0  \'96 the server hostname is taken verbatim and passed to \cf22 \cb23  iperf3 \cf19 \cb3 .\cf4                                                           \uc0\u9474 
\f1\b \cf19 Could be abused to run arbitrary commands if the user supplies something like 
\f0\b0 \cf22 \cb23  "; rm -rf /" \cf19 \cb3  on a shell\uc0\u8209 based wrapper.\cf4               \uc0\u9474 
\f1\b \cf19 Since we now use 
\f0\b0 \cf22 \cb23  ProcessBuilder \cf19 \cb3  with a 
\f2\i String[]
\f0\i0  command, arguments are not interpreted by a shell, eliminating injection.\cf4 \
  
\f1\b \cf19 Running with 
\f0\b0 \cf22 \cb23  sudo 
\f1\b \cf19 \cb3  in install scripts
\f0\b0  \'96 \cf22 \cb23  install.sh \cf19 \cb3  copies files into \cf22 \cb23  /usr/local/lib \cf19 \cb3  without checking if the user has rights.\cf4                \uc0\u9474 \cf19 If the script is run unintentionally, it can overwrite system files.\cf4                                                                 \uc0\u9474 \cf19 Prompt for confirmation before \cf22 \cb23  sudo cp \cf19 \cb3 , or better, use a package manager (e.g., \cf22 \cb23  brew \cf19 \cb3  on macOS, \cf22 \cb23  apt \cf19 \cb3 /\cf22 \cb23  yum \cf19 \cb3  on Linux) to install the binary.\cf4 \
  
\f1\b \cf19 Hard\uc0\u8209 coded temporary files
\f0\b0  \'96 none currently, but future extensions might use \cf22 \cb23  /tmp \cf19 \cb3 .\cf4                                                             \uc0\u9474 \cf19 Potential race conditions.\cf4                                                                                                           \uc0\u9474 \cf19 Use \cf22 \cb23  Files.createTempFile \cf19 \cb3  and delete on exit.\cf4 \
  
\f1\b \cf19 JNA native calls
\f0\b0  \'96 may load native libraries from the system path.\cf4                                                                               \uc0\u9474 \cf19 If a malicious DLL is placed earlier on \cf22 \cb23  PATH \cf19 \cb3 , it could be loaded.\cf4                                                                  \uc0\u9474 \cf19 Load JNA with a specific library name (\cf22 \cb23  kernel32 \cf19 \cb3 ) and restrict the search path using \cf22 \cb23  System.setProperty("jna.library.path", ...) \cf19 \cb3  if needed.\cf4 \
